ill trigger.£5/1/2012: Replacement effects that modify how a permanent enters the battlefield are now applied in the following order: control-changing effects (such as Gather Specimens), then copy effects (such as the abilities of Infinite Reflection and Clone), then all other effects.£5/1/2012: If a creature such as Clone is entering the battlefield under your control, there will be two copy effects to apply: the creature’s own and Infinite Reflection’s. No matter what order these effects are applied, the creature will be a copy of the enchanted creature when it enters the battlefield.£5/1/2012: Other enters-the-battlefield replacement abilities printed on the creature entering the battlefield won’t be applied because the creature will already be a copy of the enchanted creature at that point (and therefore it won’t have those abilities). For example, if the enchanted creature is Serra Angel, a creature that normally enters the battlefield tapped will enter the battlefield as an untapped copy of Serra Angel, and a creature that would normally enter the battlefield with counters on it will enter the battlefield as a copy of Serra Angel with no counters.£5/1/2012: External abilities may still affect how a creature enters the battlefield. For example, if your opponent controls Urabrask the Hidden, which reads, in part, “Creatures your opponents control enter the battlefield tapped,” a creature entering the battlefield under your control will be a tapped copy of the enchanted creature.£5/1/2012: If you control more than one Infinite Reflection, you can apply those copy effects in any order. Creatures you control will enter the battlefield as a copy of the one whose copy effect you apply last.','U',NULL,'0.09','0.39','1.9',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'U','无限映象','無限映象','Reflets infinis','Unendliche Spiegelung','Riflesso Infinito','無限反射','Reflexo Infinito','Бесконечное Отражение','Reflejo infinito','무한의 반사','结界～灵气','結界～靈氣','Enchantement : aura','Verzauberung — Aura','Incantesimo 